"ap-definition-en" : {"en": "The name(s) that identify the Person within a family with a common surname."}, "usage" : {"en": "Usually a first name or forename. Given to a person by his or her parents at birth or legally recognised as 'given names' through a formal process. All given names are ordered in one property so that, for example, the given name for Johann Sebastian Bach is \"Johann Sebastian\"."}, "ap-label-en" : {"en": "given name"}, "definition" : {"en": "The name(s) that identify the Person within a family with a common surname."}, "label" : {"en": "given name"},
